---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="solar-panel-sizes.html" headerVariant="policy">

<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-slate-800 text-white py-24">

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">

<div class="uppercase tracking-widest text-indigo-300 text-sm mb-4">
SOLAR EDUCATION CENTER
</div>

<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
Solar Panel Sizes & Roof Space Guide
</h1>

<p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
Understand solar panel dimensions, roof space requirements and how many panels you may need for your home.
</p>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20">

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
What Is The Size Of A Solar Panel?
</h2>

<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
Most modern residential solar panels installed in India are approximately
1.7 to 2.3 metres long and 1.0 to 1.3 metres wide, depending on manufacturer,
technology and wattage.
</p>

<div class="bg-white rounded-3xl p-8 mt-8 shadow-sm border border-slate-100">

<h3 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-4">
Typical Residential Solar Panel
</h3>

<ul class="space-y-3 text-slate-600">

<li>✓ Length: 1.7m – 2.3m</li>

<li>✓ Width: 1.0m – 1.3m</li>

<li>✓ Area: Approximately 20–30 sq ft</li>

<li>✓ Power Output: 450W – 600W+</li>

</ul>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20 bg-white">

<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-10">
How Many Panels Do You Need?
</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto">

<table class="w-full bg-white rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100">

<thead class="bg-slate-50">

<tr>

<th class="text-left p-4">System Size</th>
<th class="text-left p-4">Approx Panels</th>
<th class="text-left p-4">Roof Area</th>

</tr>

</thead>

<tbody>

<tr class="border-t">
<td class="p-4">1 kW</td>
<td class="p-4">2 Panels</td>
<td class="p-4">100 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-t">
<td class="p-4">2 kW</td>
<td class="p-4">4 Panels</td>
<td class="p-4">200 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-t">
<td class="p-4">3 kW</td>
<td class="p-4">6 Panels</td>
<td class="p-4">300 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-t">
<td class="p-4">5 kW</td>
<td class="p-4">10 Panels</td>
<td class="p-4">500 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-t">
<td class="p-4">8 kW</td>
<td class="p-4">16 Panels</td>
<td class="p-4">800 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-t">
<td class="p-4">10 kW</td>
<td class="p-4">20 Panels</td>
<td class="p-4">1000 sq ft</td>
</tr>

</tbody>

</table>

<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">
Panel quantities are illustrative examples based on modern high-efficiency residential solar panels. Actual panel counts may vary depending on panel wattage and manufacturer specifications.
</p>

</div>

</div>


</section>

<section class="py-20">

<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-10">
Roof Space Examples
</h2>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100">

<h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4">
Small Home
</h3>

<p class="text-slate-600">
1–2 kW system

<br><br>

Suitable for basic appliances and lower electricity usage.
</p>

</div>

<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100">

<h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4">
Medium Home
</h3>

<p class="text-slate-600">
3–5 kW system

<br><br>

Suitable for most Indian households.
</p>

</div>

<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100">

<h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4">
Large Home
</h3>

<p class="text-slate-600">
8–10 kW system

<br><br>

Suitable for larger families and air-conditioner usage.
</p>

<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">
Panel quantities are illustrative examples based on modern high-efficiency residential solar panels. Actual panel counts may vary depending on panel wattage and manufacturer specifications.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20 bg-white">

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
Factors Affecting Roof Requirements
</h2>

<div class="space-y-5">

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
✓ Solar panel wattage
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
✓ Roof shape and orientation
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
✓ Shading from trees and nearby buildings
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
✓ Walkway and maintenance clearances
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
✓ Local installation requirements
</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20 bg-indigo-50">

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">
Need A Personalized Recommendation?
</h2>

<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">
Our AI calculator estimates system size, roof area and savings based on your electricity bill.
</p>

<a href="index.html"
class="inline-block bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold">
Calculate My Solar Size
</a>

</div>

</section>
<!-- FOOTER -->

</BaseLayout>
